dcterms:description: User satisfaction data collected through surveys asking users to rate their experience with consumed items, providing valuable information to complement engagement data.
dcterms:title: User Satisfaction Survey Data

dcterms:description: Data capturing user interactions and engagement metrics, which serve as a proxy for user satisfaction but may not fully represent user preferences.
dcterms:title: Engagement Data

dcterms:description: Data used for training a satisfaction imputation model to predict user satisfaction levels for items they have consumed, addressing the sparsity of satisfaction signals.
dcterms:title: Satisfaction Imputation Network Data

dcterms:description: Data from a commercial recommendation platform used in live experiments to evaluate the effectiveness of the proposed reward shaping approach.
dcterms:title: Commercial Recommendation Platform Data
